### Seaman's Rules

* Rule #5: Easy way out - hard way back
    * Short-cut result in you taking the long way around
    * Pay now or pay later


### Web Servers and Web Browsers
* Web server responds with the requested web pages

![](img/WebServer.png)


### Building Web Pages
* Edit your code
* Test your code
* Send to server
* Test your page on server


### Development Loop
* Select One Feature
    * Edit
    * Test locally
    * Deploy to the web server
    * Test remote


### One-click Actions
* Files (Windows Start Bar)
* Edit (Windows Start Bar)
    * Set Open Folder to code
* Browse (Windows Start Bar)
    * Test locally (Firefox Bookmark)
    * Test remotely (Firefox Bookmark)
* Deploy (Windows Start Bar)


### Show File Extensions
* File Explorer - View Options
* File name extensions (on)


### Setup Files
* Create a folder "Documents/UNC_BACS_200/public_html/bacs200"
* Create a short-cut on the Windows Desktop
* Add to Start Bar


### Run Brackets
* Editor that knows HTML
* Windows Start Menu - Brackets
* Pin to Task Bar
* Use brackets to create a file (index.html)


### Fast Edit of Files
* Right click on HTML file
* Select "Edit with Brackets"


### Simple HTML (Page fragment)
* Headline and Paragraph

```
<h1>My Name is Inigo Montoya</h1>
<p>You killed my father.</p>
<p>Prepare to die!</p>
```


### Testing Your Local Page
* Double-click on "index.html" or short-cut
* Bookmark or F5


